About Kharkiv National Medical University

Kharkiv National Medical University is one of the oldest & best medical universities in Ukraine that was founded in 1805. This university is a member of the National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine. It has well-educated and experienced staffs who offer quality education to students with reasonable course fees. The process of{" "} MBBS admission in Ukraine is very easy. It has attained top accreditation in Ukraine by the State Accreditation Committee of Ukraine. The students{" "} can study MBBS in Ukraine {" "} in Russian and English languages.

Indian Student Admission Procedure

Indian students need to follow the below steps to take admission in the top MBBS college in Ukraine:

  • {" "} The students should contact the admission department of the University by info@ksmu.kharkov.ua and send the documents such as secondary school completion certificate & international passport or birth certificate.
  • {" "} The scanned documents are to be sent to the University by email for evaluation of eligibility.
  • {" "} The student will be granted an{" "} MBBS admission in Ukraine confirmation letter if they are eligible.
  • {" "} After receiving the confirmation letter, the students are advised to pay the first year admission fee to process the admission further.
  • {" "} The students should apply for the visa with the original receipt of the admission fee.

Eligibility Criteria of Kharkiv National Medical University

The eligibility criteria of the students who want to{" "} study MBBS in Ukraine are as follows:

  • {" "} The students should have science in their 12th standard and should have an aggregate of 50% marks in physics, chemistry, and Biology.
  • {" "} The students should be at least 17 years of age to take admission in the top MBBS college in Ukraine.
  • {" "} The students should also qualify for the NEET exam with passing marks to apply for taking admission to the{" "} best medical university in Ukraine.
  • {" "} The students should have English subject in their higher secondary.
  • {" "} The students must not be more than 25 years of age.
Requirements for MBBS Admission

The necessary documents for taking{" "} MBBS admission in Ukraine are the following:

  • {" "} A complete filled application form with all accurate details.
  • {" "} Original and photocopies of Passport.
  • {" "} Birth certificates and other mandatory certificates must be submitted to the concerned authority.
  • {" "} Passport size (3cmX4cm) photographs.
  • {" "} Original and a photocopy of mark sheets of both 10th & 12th standard
  • {" "} A scorecard of NEFT (if required)
  • {" "} Transfer certificate from the previous school
  • {" "} Leaving certificate from the concerned school
  • {" "} A certificate of code of conduct must be submitted
  • {" "} The bank copy of guardians must be submitted which indicates that they have sufficient funds to pay the fees.
  • {" "} A medical checkup certificate is also essential
